# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# italmarket — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (dev) or configure it in your host's UI (prod)
# and fill in the values. Everything here has a sensible default for the live
# italmarket.com.ar store, so leaving this file empty will still produce a
# working build against the real WooCommerce catalog.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Base URL of the WordPress/WooCommerce installation that exposes the public
# Store API under /wp-json/wc/store/v1. The site reads products, categories,
# cart and search from this host. No keys required — Store API is public.
#
# Used by:  lib/woocommerce.ts  lib/wc-store.ts  app/api/search/route.ts
#           scripts/optimize-catalog-images.mjs
WC_SITE_URL=https://italmarket.com.ar

# Optional. Port Next.js should listen on. Hostinger's Node.js hosting usually
# sets this automatically; leave it blank unless your host requires a value.
# PORT=3000

# Optional. Node environment. Hostinger's deploy pipeline sets this to
# "production" during build — do not override in normal deploys.
# NODE_ENV=production
